<item>
            <title>[DERBY-3307] NPE in PooledConnction event notification handling if a null listener is added</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3307</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If a null reference is passed in to one of the ClientPooledConnection.addXEventListener, a NPE will be thrown if an event occurs.&lt;br/&gt;
I will attach a simple repro as a patch to the test jdbc4.StatementEventsTests. I believe the situation is the same for connection event listeners.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have found no information in the specs regarding null listeners, but I assume it would be okay to ignore them.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
